From the manufacturer

Advance Your Gaming Immersion

Compatible with the latest AMD Ryzen CPUs, the ASUS ROG Strix B550-F Gaming Motherboard (Wi-Fi) delivers all-around performance for competitive PC gaming. This ASUS motherboard combines a high-end feature set with robust power delivery and effective cooling, creating a powerful and customizable motherboard designed for total gaming immersion. The latest connectivity options, super-smooth networking, and next-gen audio enhancements allow you to pick up on the subtlest of cues for a competitive edge.

Read more

Unfettered access to memory

This gaming motherboard supports four slots of dual channel DDR4 memory up to 128 GB, with ASUS OptiMem II providing the CPU unfettered access to memory bandwidth thanks to reimagined motherboard trace routing, enabling higher memory frequencies and lower latencies. Two M.2 slots, one of which supports the latest PCIe 4.0 standard, provide maximum storage flexibility and the fastest data speeds available via the 3rd Gen AMD Ryzen platform. Both M.2 slots support up to the type 22110 socket and NVM Express RAID for a performance boost.

Read more

Cooler by Design

Offering a robust power design, the B550 motherboard features 12+2 DrMOS power stages with high-quality alloy chokes and durable capacitors to provide reliable power for the latest high-core-count AMD CPUs. Digi+ power controllers offer precise memory and voltage tuning for optimal system efficiency and performance. Fanless VRM and chipset heatsinks with ASUS Stack Cool 3+ design are configurable via Fan Xpert 4 or the UEFI BIOS for a customizable thermal solution to keep your components cool under heavy load.

Read more

Blazing-fast Networking Speeds

This gaming computer motherboard offers blazing-fast wired and wireless networking speeds, with onboard WiFi 6 (802.11ax) and onboard 2.5 Gb Ethernet giving your connectivity a boost. WiFi 6 supports ultrafast wireless-networking speeds, improved capacity, and better performance in dense wireless environments for exceptional online gaming experiences. Onboard 2.5 Gb Ethernet delivers speeds that are 2.5 times faster than standard Ethernet connections, ensuring speedy file transfers, high-res video streaming, and no more fear of lag ruining a perfectly-timed takedown.

ROG SupremeFX Audio Technology

Integrated ROG SupremeFX audio technology delivers pristine audio with a flat frequency response for a neutral and detailed sound signature. Two front-panel outputs provide high-quality audio to gaming headsets, with audio-line shielding that blocks electromagnetic interference from the motherboard and add-ons for a cleaner audio signal. The motherboard also comes pre-equipped with the DTS Sound Unbound app, which uses Windows Sonic spatial technology to conjure new levels of immersion for extraordinary gaming and entertainment experiences. This innovative technology delivers audio in a virtual 3D space letting you sense the location of every sound in your environment.

Cyberpunk-inspired aesthetics

The ROG Strix B550-F Wi-Fi Gaming Motherboard embodies the ROG spirit with eye-catching cyberpunk-inspired aesthetics and customizable lighting options to make your machine truly your own. Personalize your motherboard with ASUS Aura technology, which enables full RGB lighting control and a variety of presets for embedded RGB LEDs, as well as lighting strips connected to onboard RGB headers. The addressable Gen 2 RGB header is also capable of detecting the number of LEDs on second-gen addressable RGB devices, allowing the software to automatically tailor lighting effects to specific devices and synced with Aura- capable ASUS hardware.

Read more

Product description

Style:B550-F (WI-FI)

Combining a high-end feature set and futuristic aesthetics, the ASUS ROG Strix B550-F Gaming Motherboard (Wi-Fi) is custom built for performance gaming. This ASUS motherboard is compatible with 3rd Gen AMD Ryzen CPUs, offering world-class desktop speeds to gamers, with support for dual channel DDR4 memory up to 128 GB. Two M.2 slots, including the latest PCIe 4.0, utilize the 3rd Gen AMD Ryzen platform provide to maximum storage flexibility and the fastest data speeds available, with both M.2 slots supporting up to the type 22110 socket and NVM Express RAID to deliver a boost in a performance. Onboard 2.5 Gb Ethernet delivers speeds that are 2.5 times faster than standard Ethernet connections for speedy file transfers, lag-free gaming, and high-res video streaming, while onboard WiFi 6 (802.11ax) supports ultrafast wireless-networking speeds, improved capacity, and better performance in dense wireless environments. The B550 motherboard is powered by 12+2 DrMOS power stages, with high-quality alloy chokes and durable capacitors to provide reliable power for the latest high-core-count AMD CPUs. The Fanless VRM and chipset heatsinks with ASUS Stack Cool 3+ design keep your system running reliably under heavy loads by enhancing passive cooling capacity for critical onboard components. Cyberpunk-inspired aesthetics including the distorted ROG eye logo and recessed cybertext patterning etched on the I/O shroud make this AMD Ryzen motherboard a striking centerpiece for your dream build.

SyrslyTwitch
3.0 out of 5 stars A very cool feature set for such a low price point, but there are some major flaws.
Reviewed in the United States on June 29, 2020
Style: B550-F (WI-FI)Verified Purchase
I don't have time to really write a proper review for this at this time, but rest asured I will update this as I figure things out.

Pros:
+ Lots of features, including a magnetic wifi 6 antenna!
+ Works with Ryzen 3900X out-of-box.
+ 2 M.2 slots with covers and included mounting screws!
+ Great lighting design with support for LED strips.
+ Nice-looking back IO layout with no separate back plate, thankfully.

Cons:
- Half the features don't work as well as hoped.
- Ryzen 3900X works, but the overclocking options are limited a bit by the dated bios.
- Wifi 6 but the bios doesn't even use a wired connection, meaning updating the bios is a PITA.
- While you have 2 M.2 slots, using either slot will disable your _56 SATA ports!
- Manual/online docs are lacking any information on troubleshooting the problems I've encountered and do not provide proper mappings for each port on the board. I eventually figured out most ports, but some are still a bit of a mystery. Seems like this could be due to the board being somewhat new.
- PCIE safeslot latch is easily breakable and may cause harm to your GPU if you're not extremely careful.

Overall, while it's a great price point, I can't recommend it at this time if you use more than one M.2 drive, use a M.2 drive with any SATA drives, or want to use the newest Asus bios features. (The 370-Pro is way better than this bios-wise.) It's also a bit of a PITA to get the GPU out of this thing without breaking off the safeslot latch, which is a major flaw since you may have to take out the GPU multiple times during setup and during the inevitable troubleshooting.

ASUS B-550 F Gaming (WiFi).
Not going to add anything you can already read in the description, but instead things you may not notice until it’s in your hands.
Bios is updated out the box to run 3rd Gen Ryzen. Everything is easily accessible. Power supply is meant to support 8+4 pin especially if you wanna overclock. Keep that I mind. But will work just fine if you only have an 8 pin power supply. Just make sure you’re have enough wattage for what your running. 600w is enough for most set ups. Comes with an I/O port shield already and has plenty of I/O ports built in as well as a BIOS flash USB port to update the BIOS without a graphics card and monitor which can come in handy. Front I/O ports are located at the bottom right like most motherboards. It does have 2 RGB addressable headers, one at the top and one at the bottom for really nice wiring. Logo on the top left of MOBO lights up in RGB. Plenty of Fan ports which is always good. Asus crate software is nice and convenient to update all drivers in one spot. Bluetooth works great. WiFi, meh maybe it’s my distance from the router. I’d have to play with it more see if it’s the antenna or my router location but I can’t seem to hit over 40mps when I have much more. I’d imagine most people would run hardwire but then again you wouldn’t be buying the WiFi version. All in all it’s a solid motherboard. Definitely would recommend to anyone looking to build a pc. Only bad thing is the price, for a b550 it’s in the same price range as x570. So depending on what prices are out there maybe an x570 wouldn’t be a bad option.

Comes with an I/O port shield already and has plenty of I/O ports built in as well as a BIOS flash USB port to update the BIOS without a graphics card and monitor which can come in handy. This was part of my first build in at least 10 years. Let me say everything has changed; Hard Drives, Cases/Towers, lightning speed of modern hardware. I had an old Asus Mobo that a friend had built me several years ago. Since then, the only other Mobo I've had was an MSI which was also nice. I paired this with my Ryzen 7 3700x, 64gb RAM, and a 1660 super graphics card. This exceeds all my needs. Gaming wasn't even my main priority. If gaming was my main priority I would have gone with a better GPU. I got this because it's future proof (probably for the next 3-5 years) and will be able to handle my work and casual video and photo editing.
The only con has always been Asus' support. Just the other day the DL link to update BIOS was not working. Also, on a clean install of Windows 10, I really struggled to get the WIFI and Ethernet drivers to work. The disk included with the case and what was on their website was no help. I had to do a lot of searching. Once it's up and running it's fine, but the initial set up and their support is a struggle.
